    <mj-section css-class="mj_section" background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="             
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Groww plans IPO at $8B valuation</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.longandshort.com/email/images/ls-jan-21-1.png" alt="Groww plans IPO at $8B valuation" href="https://www.altdaily.co" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Billionbrains Garage Ventures, the parent of fintech platform Groww, is <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-21-01-2025-h1-1-preparing-for-an-ipo" target="_blank">preparing for an IPO</a>. The firm is targeting a valuation of $7-8 billion. Backed by Microsoft CEO Satya Nadella and major investors like Ribbit Capital and Tiger Global, Groww has over 50 million customers. The IPO could raise around $750 million. Banks such as JPMorgan and Kotak Mahindra are reportedly involved in the deal. India's IPO market remains strong, with over $20 billion raised last year, making it the second-busiest market after the U.S.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- Content sections -->
    <mj-section css-class="mj_section" background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-spacer height="0px" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="              
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2; 
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Trump tariffs may hurt GM in Canada</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4;filter:blur(5px);">
          GM Canada's president warned that Trump's <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-21-01-2025-h2-2-proposed-25-tariffs" target="_blank">proposed 25% tariffs</a> on Canadian imports could disrupt supply chains and raise vehicle prices. Canada imports about 50% of vehicles from the U.S. by value and relies heavily on U.S. auto parts. GM has two Ontario assembly plants that build Chevrolet Silverado pickup trucks and electric vans for commercial use. Depending on tariff details, the company may need to reassess operations. Canada's electric vehicle targets are also seen as unrealistic, adding more pressure. If imposed, tariffs could increase costs and impact demand, while Canada is prepared to retaliate with counter-tariffs.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
